(40, 25, 19, 45, 14, 7, 12, 'reckoneth with them', 'Judgment and Accountability', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of accountability before the Lord. Matthew 25:19 speaks of reckoning with servants, while Romans 14:12 states that everyone will give account of himself to God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 19, 40, 18, 23, 24, 'reckoneth with them', 'Accountability of Servants', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of reckoning with servants. In Matthew 25:19, the lord reckons with his servants, while in Matthew 18:23-24, the king begins to take account of his servants.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 19, 42, 16, 1, 2, 'reckoneth with them', 'Accountability in Stewardship', 'This connection highlights the theme of accountability in stewardship. Both passages emphasize the necessity of giving an account for one''s actions, as seen in ''reckoneth with them'' and ''give an account of thy stewardship.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 19, 40, 24, 48, 48, NULL, 'Servants and Delay of Coming', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of the lord''s return and the expectation of reckoning. The first passage speaks of the lord coming after a long time, while the second reflects on the potential for a servant to think the lord delays his coming.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
